<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <header>
        <title>
            Containers in Bootstrap
        </title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    </header>
    <body>
        <h1>
            Containers in Bootstrap
        </h1>
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <h1>
                Container-Fluid 
            </h1>
            <p>
               Container-Fluid is a Bootstrap layout class that creates a full-width container, spanning 100% of the viewport width across all device breakpoints. Unlike the standard .container, which has fixed max-widths and centered content, .container-fluid provides continuous, edge-to-edge responsiveness with default horizontal padding of 15px. 
           </p>
        </div>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>
                Container
            </h1>
            <p>
               In Bootstrap, containers are a fundamental layout element used to contain, pad, and align content within a given viewport, and are essential for using the grid system. 
            </p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
